This is the first poem that I ever memorized.  I must have been sixteen at the time.  I remember reading a lot of Dorothy Parker that year.  My friend Michael introduced me to her work, and  I credit him for much of my early understanding of poetry.  He also taught me to appreciate the nuances in different interpretations of Chopin's Nocturnes. #roman

Life before sixteen was a bit of a fog, but M. was one of the people who drew me out of it. #roman

